bug.short_desc: There seems to be some missing icons.
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1279333 Screenshot
I've installed gimagereader-gtk using dnf and, apparently, there are some missing icons in buttons and menu items, see attached screenshot. I'm using Fedora 25 Workstation (Gnome).
Mh looks like something changed in Gtk results in the icons failing to load from the embedded resources... Will need to look into it.
